The White House issued a statement on September 14, 2009, expressing sadness over the passing of Jody Powell, who served as Press Secretary to President Carter. The statement praised Powell for his service during a challenging period and highlighted his grace and good humor in carrying out his duties. The current Press Secretary also mentioned that Powell provided valuable advice and support at the beginning of their own tenure. The statement concluded by expressing condolences to Powell's family and keeping them in thoughts and prayers.